🔷 Typing Props in React

🧾 Using Interface

```tsx
interface UserProps {
  name: string;
  age: number;
}

function User({ name, age }: UserProps) {
  return (
    <h2>
      {name} - {age}
    </h2>
  );
}
```

📌 Strongly typed props

------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

🔷 Optional Props

```tsx
interface Props {
  name: string;
  age?: number;
}
```

`?` makes prop optional

------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

🔷 Typing useState

```tsx
const [count, setCount] = useState<number>(0);
```

For object:

```tsx
interface User {
  name: string;
  age: number;
}

const [user, setUser] = useState<User>({
  name: "",
  age: 0
});
```

