🔷 TypeScript vs PropTypes

| TypeScript              | PropTypes        |
| ----------------------- | ---------------- |
| Compile-time checking   | Runtime checking |
| Strong typing           | Basic validation |
| Better IDE support      | Limited          |
| Used in production apps | Mostly legacy    |

📌 Modern apps prefer TypeScript

------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

🔷 Generic Components Example

```tsx
interface ListProps<T> {
  items: T[];
  render: (item: T) => React.ReactNode;
}

function List<T>({ items, render }: ListProps<T>) {
  return <>{items.map(render)}</>;
}
```

📌 Powerful for reusable components

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

🔷 Type Aliases vs Interface

```tsx
type User = {
  name: string;
  age: number;
};
```

| Interface             | Type            |
| --------------------- | --------------- |
| Extendable            | Flexible        |
| Preferred for objects | Good for unions |

